Explanation:

The problem requires finding the number of set bits in an integer. We can solve this problem using bit manipulation. The algorithm uses a while loop to iterate until the integer becomes 0. Inside the loop, it performs a bitwise AND operation with the number minus 1 to clear all the set bits, and then increments the count variable. This process continues until the integer becomes 0, at which point the count represents the number of set bits.

The time complexity is O(log(n)) because the loop iterates log2(n) times, where n is the input integer. The space complexity is O(1) because the algorithm uses a constant amount of space for the count variable. The energy implications are low because the algorithm performs bitwise operations, which are computationally efficient and consume minimal energy compared to other operations.

